wikipedia_page.main: Henry Beagley (born 7 January 1805) was an English professional cricketer who played first-class cricket from 1825 to 1833.  He was a brother of Thomas Beagley and an occasional wicket-keeper who was mainly associated with Hampshire.  He made 6 known appearances in first-class matches including 3 for The Bs from 1825 to 1832.
